     Baggage

     Weight - Dimensions

     * Baggage

Weight - Dimensions

   ü
   Is your checked baggage included?

   Booked a flight with our Eco Budget fare? Checked baggage isn’t
   included. Pay at least 24 hours before departure and save up to 20% on
   your first checked bag. Pay for my bags now >

   FOR BOOKINGS MADE AS OF OCTOBER 2, 2018

Between Canada and U.S., Domestic flights within Canada

   Select the applicable type of baggage: This field will display new
   content. [- Choose -__________________________]

   CAPTION: Baggage weight allowed according to the class.
   Between Canada, U.S. and Domestic flights within Canada.

   Each passenger is permitted one piece of carry-on bag and one personal
   item, subject to size and weight restrictions. The total combined
   weight must not exceed 10 kg.

          Economy Class Option Plus*   Club Class
   Weight 10 kg (22 lb) 10 kg (22 lb) 15 kg (33 lb)
   *not available for Domestic flights within Canada

   CAPTION: Carry-on

   Quantity 1 bag per person.
   Dimensions 23 x 40 x 51 cm (9 x 16 x 20 in) (including wheels and
   handles)
   Cost Free
   Excess baggage charges Any carry-on bag that exceeds the above weight
   or size cannot be carried on and must be checked. Excess charges may
   apply. Payable at Air Transat check-in counter.
   Details Some examples of carry-on items: Carry-on bag; Roller bag;
   Backpack; Cat or small dog in its carrier; Folding strollers; Booster
   seat; Equipment / infant beds (BedBox® etc.); Small musical instrument.
   Exceptions Some examples of items exempt from the carry-on
   restrictions:
     * Essential medical equipment (CPAP, bags with essential health
       items, etc.)
     * Diaper bag (for passengers with children under 2 years of age)
     * Child safety seat for use on board the plane
     * Mobility aids (crutches, wheelchair, walker, etc.)
     * Funeral urn

   CAPTION: Personal Items

   Quantity 1 per person.
   Dimensions 16 x 33 x 43 cm (6 x 13 x 17 in)
   Cost Free
   Details Some examples of personal items: Handbag or briefcase; Camera
   or camera case (can contain items such as spare lenses in addition to
   the camera); Laptop computer bag; Bag of items from the airport and the
   duty-free shop; Wedding dress; Sports ball, small sports racquet (e.g.
   squash, badminton);  Garment, diplomatic or consular bag.

   Additional Information

   For information on liquids, gels and/or aerosols restrictions, please
   refer to Security and restrictions.

   Fragile or perishable articles must be placed in carry-on baggage, as
   these items will not be accepted as checked baggage. These items
   include:
     * Jewellery; Money; Silverware; Electronics; Laptop
       computers; Personal audio/video devices; Negotiable
       documents; Securities; Samples of business documents; Other
       valuables
     * Smoking materials
          + 1 lighter per passenger, packed in the allowable 1 plastic bag
            per passenger (due to liquid content).
          + No lighters in checked baggage
          + 1 book of matches per passenger, carried only on your person
          + Electronic cigarettes: stowed unused in carry-on baggage at
            all times. Carriage in checked baggage is prohibited.
          + Specific country restrictions may also apply.

   You may carry Epi-Pens or hypodermic needles only for personal medical
   use. The needle guard must be in place and the needle must be
   accompanied by the medication in its original labeled container or with
   a signed doctor's certificate.
   Select the currency: This field will display new content.
   [- Choose -____________]

   Baggage fees, maximum weight and number of bags allowed

   CAPTION: ECONOMY CLASS - FLIGHT ONLY

   Pieces of baggage ECO BUDGET ECO STANDARD & ECO FLEX
   First baggage 23 kg, $25/$30^ 3 23 kg, included
   Second baggage^ 1 23 kg, $40/$50^ 2 ECO STANDARD: 23 kg, $40/$50^ 2
   ECO FLEX: 23 kg, included
   Additional baggage (each)^1 23 kg, $200 23 kg, $200

   CAPTION: ECONOMY CLASS - TRANSAT PACKAGES AND TRANSAT CRUISE PACKAGES

   Pieces of baggage  PACKAGES  CRUISES
   First baggage   23 kg, included   28 kg, included
   (includes voucher for extra 5 kg allowed)
   Second baggage^ 1   23 kg, $40/$50^ 2   23 kg, $40/$50^ 2
   Additional baggage (each)^1   23 kg, $200   23 kg, $200

   CAPTION: OPTION PLUS - FLIGHT ONLY

        Pieces of baggage          ECO BUDGET      ECO STANDARD & ECO FLEX
          First baggage          23 kg, included     23 kg, included
        Second baggage^ 1        23 kg, $40/$50^ 2   23 kg, included
   Additional baggage (each)^1   23 kg, $200         23 kg, $200

   CAPTION: OPTION PLUS - TRANSAT PACKAGES AND TRANSAT CRUISE PACKAGES

        Pieces of baggage          PACKAGES           CRUISES
          First baggage          23 kg, included
    28 kg, included
   (includes voucher for extra 5 kg allowed)
         Second baggage          23 kg, included   23 kg, included
   Additional baggage (each)^1   23 kg, $200       23 kg, $200

   CAPTION: CLUB CLASS

        Pieces of baggage         CLUB CLASS
          First baggage          25 kg, included
         Second baggage          25 kg, included
   Additional baggage (each)^1   25 kg, $200
   ^1Second bag (if not included) and additional pieces of checked baggage
   are subject to space availability.
   ^2Prices for the second piece of checked baggage vary between $40 if
   prepaid and $50 if paid within 24 hours of departure.
   ^3Prices for the first piece of checked baggage vary between $25 if
   prepaid and $30 if paid within 24 hours of departure.
   Prices and weights indicated are valid per flight segment. Applicable
   taxes are not included.

   CAPTION: More details about checked baggage

     Dimensions   Length + width + height must not exceed 158 cm (62 in)
   Excess baggage

   A $75* fee will apply on each piece of checked baggage exceeding the
   maximum weight allowed.
   *USD: $75 / EUR: €60 / GBP: £49
   Details

   Please take a moment to review the contents of your luggage, as some
   items may be restricted and pose a potential hazard on board the
   aircraft.

   If any individual piece weighs more than 32 kg (70 lb), contact our
   Cargo departmentWill open in a separate browser window for details at
   least 72 hours prior to departure.

   Fragile or perishable items will not be accepted in checked baggage.
   These items include:
     * Medication or medical devices
     * Currency
     * Jewellery
     * Silverware
     * Electronics
     * Laptop computers
     * Personal audio/video devices
     * Marketable securities
     * Business samples
     * Other valuables (other than clothing)
       Any such items declared or found in checked baggage shall be
       subject to removal prior to the baggage in question being accepted
       for carriage by the Carrier.

   The Carrier shall not be liable for damage to fragile, valuable or
   perishable items where such damage resulted from the inherent defect,
   quality, or vice of the item in question. Unsuitably or inadequately
   packed items will be accepted at the Carrier’s discretion and, where
   accepted, compensation may be denied as a result of the aforementioned
   factors. The Carrier assumes no liability for the delay in delivery of
   any perishable items accepted as checked baggage unless it has failed
   to take all reasonable measures to avoid such delay.
   See Liability limitations below.

   Baggage fees, maximum weight and number of bags allowed

   CAPTION: ECONOMY CLASS - FLIGHT ONLY

   Pieces of baggage ECO BUDGET ECO STANDARD & ECO FLEX
   First baggage 23 kg, €20/€24^3 23 kg, included
   Second baggage 23 kg, €32/€40^2 ECO STANDARD: 23 kg, €32/€40^2
   ECO FLEX: 23 kg, included
   Additional baggage (each)^1 23 kg, €160 23 kg, €160

   CAPTION: ECONOMY CLASS - TRANSAT PACKAGES AND TRANSAT CRUISE PACKAGES

   Pieces of baggage  PACKAGES  CRUISES
