   CAPTION: About the baggage policy that applies to children's Car Seat.

   Quantity 1 per child/infant
   Size Regular size
   Weight Regular weight
   Cost Free within size, piece and weight limits. One car or booster seat
   accepted at no charge per travelling child/infant. Additional car or
   booster seats are subject to excess baggage charges, if the free
   baggage allowance (weight and/or pieces permitted) is exceeded.
   Details

   Children under 18 kg (40 lb) will be safer and more comfortable on
   board when secured in an approved car seat or C.A.R.E.S.* device.

   Note: Booster seats or vest-type restraint systems do not provide
   sufficient protection on airplanes for small children. Thus, they are
   not approved for airline use!

   Approved car seats:

   Canadian-made: The seat must be manufactured after Jan. 1, 1981 and
   must display inspection label.
     * CMVSS 213 or 213.1 Canada

   U.S.A.-made: The seat must be manufactured after Feb. 26, 1985 and must
   display these labels:
     * This child restraint system conforms to all applicable Federal
       motor Vehicle Safety Standards.
       AND

     * This restraint is certified for use in motor vehicles and aircraft.

   Europe-made: Restraint system manufactured to the UN ECE standard
   (Europe) must bear two labels:
     * An international approval label consisting of a circle surrounding
       the letter “E” followed by the distinguishing number of the country
       that has granted approval (reflects UN standard ECE R 44, revision
       03 or later).

     * A second label that states it is approved for use in aircraft.

   Car seats manufactured in any other country are not approved for use on
   board.
   *C.A.R.E.S (child aviation restraint system): The AmSafe C.A.R.E.S
   device can be used by children between the ages of 1 and 4, weighing
   between 10-20 kg (22-44 lb) and whose height is 100 cm (40 in) or less.


