       Any such items declared or found in checked baggage shall be
       subject to removal prior to the baggage in question being accepted
       for carriage by the Carrier.

   The Carrier shall not be liable for damage to fragile, valuable or
   perishable items where such damage resulted from the inherent defect,
   quality, or vice of the item in question. Unsuitably or inadequately
   packed items will be accepted at the Carrier’s discretion and, where
   accepted, compensation may be denied as a result of the aforementioned
   factors. The Carrier assumes no liability for the delay in delivery of
   any perishable items accepted as checked baggage unless it has failed
   to take all reasonable measures to avoid such delay.
   See Liability limitations below.

   For more information, consult our dangerous goods and prohibited items
   section.

   Infants travelling on an adult's lap do not have a baggage allowance;
   however, 1 stroller and 1 car seat per child/infant are accepted free
   of charge. No substitutions permitted. Additional items (such as a
   playpen, booster seat, additional car seat, etc.) exceeding your free
   checked baggage allowance (weight, size and/or number of pieces
   permitted) will be subject to excess baggage charges. Parent/guardian
   may carry diaper bag in addition to regular carry-on, containing
   supplies needed for duration of flight.
   Select a type of baby and child equipment below for the baggage policy:
   This field will display new content.
   [- Choose -_______________________]

   CAPTION: About the baggage policy that applies to children's Car Seat.

   Quantity 1 per child/infant
   Size Regular size
   Weight Regular weight
   Cost Free within size, piece and weight limits. One car or booster seat
   accepted at no charge per travelling child/infant. Additional car or
   booster seats are subject to excess baggage charges, if the free
   baggage allowance (weight and/or pieces permitted) is exceeded.
   Details

   Children under 18 kg (40 lb) will be safer and more comfortable on
   board when secured in an approved car seat or C.A.R.E.S.* device.

   Note: Booster seats or vest-type restraint systems do not provide
   sufficient protection on airplanes for small children. Thus, they are
   not approved for airline use!

   Approved car seats:

   Canadian-made: The seat must be manufactured after Jan. 1, 1981 and
   must display inspection label.
     * CMVSS 213 or 213.1 Canada

   U.S.A.-made: The seat must be manufactured after Feb. 26, 1985 and must
   display these labels:
     * This child restraint system conforms to all applicable Federal
       motor Vehicle Safety Standards.
       AND

     * This restraint is certified for use in motor vehicles and aircraft.

   Europe-made: Restraint system manufactured to the UN ECE standard
   (Europe) must bear two labels:
     * An international approval label consisting of a circle surrounding
       the letter “E” followed by the distinguishing number of the country
       that has granted approval (reflects UN standard ECE R 44, revision
       03 or later).

     * A second label that states it is approved for use in aircraft.

   Car seats manufactured in any other country are not approved for use on
   board.
   *C.A.R.E.S (child aviation restraint system): The AmSafe C.A.R.E.S
   device can be used by children between the ages of 1 and 4, weighing
   between 10-20 kg (22-44 lb) and whose height is 100 cm (40 in) or less.


   CAPTION: About the baggage policy that applies to children's folding
   playpen.

   Size Regular size
   Weight Regular weight
   Cost If the playpen and all other checked baggage exceed the free
   baggage allowance (weight, size and/or number of pieces permitted),
   excess baggage charges will apply.
   Details

   Please ensure that equipment is properly wrapped/secured for transport
   to prevent loss or damage.

   Not accepted as carry-on baggage.

   CAPTION: About the baggage policy that applies to children's stroller.

   Quantity 1 per child/infant
   Size Regular size
   Weight Maximum: 23Kg
   Cost Free within size, piece and weight limits. One stroller accepted
   at no charge per travelling child/infant. Additional strollers are
   subject to excess baggage charges, if the free baggage allowance
   (weight and/or pieces permitted) is exceeded.
   Details Please ensure that strollers are properly wrapped/secured for
   transport to prevent loss or damage.
   Gate Delivery Service: At most airports, passengers travelling with a
   small, fully collapsible and lightweight stroller will qualify to take
   it right to the boarding gate and collect it at the aircraft door at
   the end of their flight.
   Strollers must not weigh more than 11 kg, nor exceed 60 cm in depth and
   108 cm in length.
   ​This service is not available in Cancun, Punta Cana, Cuba, Portugal,
   Spain, Rome, London or on connecting flights. Complimentary strollers
   will be available on arrival, in Portugal, London and Spain, except in
   Barcelona.
   Large, heavy, non-collapsible, double and multi-piece strollers cannot
   be accepted for gate delivery and will be delivered to the arrivals
   baggage hall (oversize carousel) at the final destination.

   CAPTION: About the baggage policy that applies to children's strollers,
   carry-on baggage.

   Details Compact, foldable strollers that do not exceed our standard
   carry-on dimensions (23 x 40 x 51 cm / 9 x 16 x 20 inches) may be taken
   into the passenger cabin in lieu of a regular carry-on bag.

   Humanitarian donations will be included in your regular baggage
   allowance. If the combined items and baggage exceed the free baggage
   allowance per person, excess baggage charges will apply. In addition,
   passengers are responsible for any import procedures or applicable
   customs duties at the destination.

   If you wish to send donations to charitable organizations that Air
   Transat supports, you can do so via our local cargo facility.Will open
   in a separate browser window

   Donations must be brought a minimum of 72 hours before departure to the
   local Air Transat cargo area. As cargo facilities are not located in
   the airport terminal, please call ahead for the location, rates and
   related information.

   Check with the Department of Agriculture of your destination country
   for regulations and restrictions in effect with regard to importing or
   exporting food products.

   Please note that it is prohibited to bring meat, dairy and many other
   food products into the European Union.

   For more information, see the travelling with food products section.

