   CAPTION: Baggage policy that applies to bicycles or unicycles.

   Quantity

   Given that space is limited, we strongly recommend that passengers
   prepay for the transportation of their bicycles up to 72 hours prior to
   departure by contacting our Booking Centre.
   Cost

   75 $ CAD
   (USD: $75 / EUR: €60 / GBP: £49)
   Price per item per flight segment. An oversize plastic bag, available
   at all Air Transat check-in counters, is included.
   Details

   Maximum weight 32 kg (70 lb) (including bicycle bag/box).

   The bicycle must be placed in a sturdy bag or box.

   In preparation for travel, handlebars must be turned sideways and
   secured, the tires deflated, and the pedals removed. A bicycle helmet
   is accepted free of charge.

   Oversize bicycles or tandems: As security facilities vary between
   airports, we suggest these items be shipped via cargo, as security
   facilities vary between airports and may not accommodate larger items,
   which could result in refusal of acceptance.

   Children’s tricycles: 3-wheeled children’s tricycles are accepted at no
   charge when travelling with a child.

   Lithium battery powered bicycles: are not accepted as passenger baggage
   at check-in (even if the battery is removed). Please contact our Cargo
   department Will open in a separate browser window for information.

   We strongly recommend that passengers speak to their travel agents or
   our booking centre to make arrangements for the transfer of their
   sports equipment to their hotels.

   For groups of 10 passengers or more travelling with bicycles, please
   contact us in advance as special arrangements may be required
   (additional charges may apply).Email: request@airtransat.com

