   CAPTION: Baggage policy that applies to Wedding dress.

   Quantity 1 per person
     Size   Not exceeding 135 x 60 cm (53 x 23.5 in)
    Weight  Regular weight
     Cost   Free of charge
   Details

   Exceptionally, a wedding dress in a non-rigid garment bag, with
   measurements not to exceed 135 x 60 cm (53 x 23.5 in), may be carried
   on board, and can be laid out or gently rolled up in the overhead bin.

   There are no closet facilities on board our aircraft.

   The dress may be carried in addition to a regular-sized carry-on bag.

   Select an option below for the baggage policy: This field will display
   new content. [- Choose -_____________________________]

   CAPTION: Baggage policy that applies to electronic cigarette and
   nicotine inhaler.

   Details Electronic cigarettes are allowed provided they remain stowed
   and unused in your carry-on baggage. Carriage in checked baggage is
   prohibited. Specific country restrictions may also apply.

   CAPTION: Baggage policy that applies to Laptop computer.

   Quantity 1 per person
     Size   Standard laptop case
    Weight  Regular weight
     Cost   Free of charge
   Details

   The laptop may be carried in addition to a regular-sized carry-on bag.

   See Liability limitations below.

   CAPTION: Baggage policy that applies to Urn (human remains).

   Size May be transported in your carry-on bag (23 x 40 x 51 cm (9 x 16 x
   20 in) including wheels and handles) or in your checked baggage.
   Weight Regular weight
   Cost Free of charge within weight and size limits
   Details

   The urn must be able to pass the x-ray at the security checkpoint (in
   carry-on or checked baggage). If it can be x-rayed and security can see
   the contents, it will be allowed in the cabin. If the contents cannot
   be viewed by x-ray, the urn will be refused for transport and must be
   shipped via alternate means such as air cargo or mail.

   Urns made of plastic, cardboard or cloth are recommended.

   Passengers must present the cremation and the death certificates at
   check-in as well as security checkpoints.

   CAPTION: Baggage policy that applies to knee defenders.

   Details Knee defenders and/or other similar devices restricting seat
   recline are not permitted for use on board Air Transat or our partner
   airlines.

   CAPTION: Baggage policy that applies to lithium batteries.

   Details Air Transat will not accept any Small lithium battery-powered
   vehicles in either checked baggage or carry-on baggage due to safety
   concerns associated to the lithium batteries that power them.
     * Vehicles not accepted include hoverboards, electric skateboards,
       airwheels, mini-Segways and balance wheels.

   Please click here for lithium battery powered mobility aids.

Between Canada and South destinations

