   CAPTION: Baggage policy that applies to musical instrument, carry-on.

     Economy Class
   Dimensions 23 x 40 x 51 cm (9 x 16 x 20 in) (including wheels and
   handles)
   Weight 10 kg (22 lb)
   Cost Free within size, piece and weight limits
   Details

   Instruments exceeding this size or weight must be checked. It is
   important to note that a musical instrument in the cabin replaces the
   carry-on baggage allowed.

   CAPTION: Baggage policy that applies to musical instrument (checked
   baggage).

   Weight Maximum 23 kg (51 lb)
   Cost If the musical instrument exceeds the quantity/dimensions/weight
   of the carry on baggage allowance, it becomes part of your checked
   baggage allowance, which when exceeded is subject to any applicable
   excess baggage charges.
   Details

   To prevent any damage, we advise storing the musical instrument in a
   protective hard case.

   Stowage space in the cabin is very limited, therefore not available for
   the transportation of musical instruments.

   For information on individual pieces of baggage exceeding 32 kg (70 lb)
   in weight, contact our Cargo departmentWill open in a separate browser
   window.

   It is highly recommended that you purchase travel insurance prior to
   your trip, to cover all such goods. Consult your travel or insurance
   agent.

   CAPTION: Baggage policy that applies to musical instrument occupying a
   purchased seat.

   Details This service is not offered on Air Transat flights.

   For more information, please refer to Pets and service dogs.

   In addition to your checked baggage allowance, we will accept at no
   charge 1 select sporting item up to 20 kg (44 lb) per passenger from
   the list below (valid items are shown as free).

   Please note that you may not substitute personal baggage or any other
   equipment for your free sporting item. If you want to bring an item not
   listed below, it will be included in your regular baggage allowance and
   excess baggage charges may apply.

   If you booked a package, be aware that charges may apply for the land
   transfer of sporting equipment to hotels at some destinations. Please
   ensure that equipment is properly wrapped/secured for transport to
   prevent loss or damage.

   Please note that hockey equipment is considered part of a passenger’s
   baggage allowance and subject to regular baggage fees. One bag and a
   maximum of two sticks taped together count as one piece of baggage
   towards the maximum number of checked bags allowed by the fare type.

   We recommend passengers purchase additional insurance.
   Select a type of sporting equipment below for the baggage policy. This
   field will display new content.
   [- Choose -____________________________________________]

   CAPTION: Baggage policy that applies to bicycles or unicycles.

   Quantity

   Given that space is limited, we strongly recommend that passengers
   prepay for the transportation of their bicycles up to 72 hours prior to
   departure by contacting our Booking Centre.
   For Cuba: Prepay for the transportation is mandatory.
   Cost

   50 $ CAD
   (USD: $50 / EUR: €40 / GBP: £32)
   Price per item per flight segment. An oversize plastic bag, available
   at all Air Transat check-in counters, is included.
   Details

   Maximum weight 32 kg (70 lb) (including bicycle bag/box).

   The bicycle must be placed in a sturdy bag or box.

   In preparation for travel, handlebars must be turned sideways and
   secured, the tires deflated, and the pedals removed. A bicycle helmet
   is accepted free of charge.

   Oversize bicycles or tandems: As security facilities vary between
   airports, we suggest these items be shipped via cargo, as security
   facilities vary between airports and may not accommodate larger items,
   which could result in refusal of acceptance.

   Children’s tricycles: 3-wheeled children’s tricycles are accepted at no
   charge when travelling with a child.

   Lithium battery powered bicycles: are not accepted as passenger baggage
   at check-in (even if the battery is removed). Please contact our Cargo
   department Will open in a separate browser window for information.

   We strongly recommend that passengers speak to their travel agents or
   our booking centre to make arrangements for the transfer of their
   sports equipment to their hotels.

   For groups of 10 passengers or more travelling with bicycles, please
   contact us in advance as special arrangements may be required
   (additional charges may apply). Email: request@airtransat.com

   CAPTION: Baggage policy that applies to Canoes and kayaks.

   Details

   Canoes and kayaks are not accepted at check-in counters, however
   our Cargo department Will open in a separate browser window will be
   pleased to assist you. Transportation charges apply.


